{{orphan|date=December 2017}} '''Ronald "Ron" Amundson''' (born 1946) is an American philosopher<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aaas.org/news/2017-aaas-fellows-recognized-advancing-science |title=2017 AAAS Fellows |publisher=aaas.org |accessdate=December 22, 2017}}</ref> currently Professor Emeritus at [[University of Hawaii Hilo]], retired since 2012,<ref name="UH">{{Cite web |url=http://hilo.hawaii.edu/keaohou/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/KeKalahea-Amundson-2012.pdf |title=KeKalahea |publisher=hawaii.edu |accessdate=December 22, 2017}}</ref> and an Elected Fellow of the [[American Association for the Advancement of Science]].<ref name="AAAS">{{Cite web |url=https://hilo.hawaii.edu/news/press/release/2074 |title=Amundson named AAAS Fellow |date=December 21, 2017 |publisher=hawaii.edu |accessdate=December 22, 2017}}</ref>
==Education== He earned his B.A. and Ph.D at University of Hawaii in 1975.<ref name="UH"/>
==Research== His interests are [[evolutionary biology]] and he is recognized for his book ''The Changing Role of the Embryo in Evolutionary Thought'' (2005, {{isbn|0521806992}})<ref name="AAAS"/> currently held in 592 libraries.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n80155112/ |title=Amundson, Ron |publisher=[[WorldCat]] |accessdate=December 22, 2017}}</ref>
