{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox person |name = Sirio Carrapa |image = Master Sirio.JPG |caption = Sirio Carrapa |birth_date = {{birth-date and age|May 12, 1952}} |birth_place = [[Borgagne]], [[Italy]] |death_date = |death_place = |other_names = |known_for = [[Guru]] of [[Surat Shabd Yoga]] or with other name Nada Yoga |occupation = [[Ayurveda|Ayurvedic]] therapist and teacher |nationality = Italian }}
'''Sirio Carrapa''' (born 12 May 1952 in [[Borgagne]]) is an [[Italy|Italian]] teacher and practitioner of [[mysticism]] and [[Surat Shabd Yoga]] in the [[Sant Mat]] tradition. He was a disciple of [[Kirpal Singh]] and [[Sant Ajaib Singh|Ajaib Singh]], and he is acknowledged as a spiritual Master ("[[Sant (religion)|Sant]]" or [[Satguru]]), carrying on the work of his Masters.<ref>[http://de.france-sante.org/informationen-sekte+guru+freiheit+der+religion+sektierertum-PSYSECT-gesundheit.php German language summary about guruship, Master Sirio elnliste here as well as contemporary Western Gurus of Sant Mat, successor of Kirpal Singh and Ajaib Sing]</ref><ref>[https://medium.com/sant-mat-radhasoami-books/guru-lineage-charts-sant-mat-radhasoami-surat-shabd-yoga-kabir-sikh-dadu-dariya-tulsi-sahib-a2cb6a98bf31 Guru lineage chart of Surat Shabd Yoga]</ref> He is also an expert in [[Ayurveda]].{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}
== Biography == He was born on 12 May, in 1952 in Borgagne, which is in one of the southernmost regions of Italy, [[Apulia]]. He lived there with his parents and four siblings until the age of 10, then in 1962 the family moved to [[Milan]]. He lived there until he moved to Tuscany, in the village [[Ribolla]] ([[Province of Grosseto|Grosseto]]) in 1979, where he founded the ''[[Sant Bani Ashram (Ribolla)|Sant Bani Ashram]]''.<ref>Most of the information about his life can be found in his autobiography ''Il Cammino Verso L'Illuminazione'' (The Path towards Enlightenment) published by M.I.R. Edizioni. {{ISBN|88-88282-55-6}}</ref> [[File:Ajaib e sirio.jpg|thumbnail|[[Sant Ajaib Singh|Sant Ajaib]] and Sirio Carrapa in Ribolla]]
