'''Yu Gam-dong''' ([[Hangul]]: 유감동; [[Hanja]]: 兪甘同) was a [[Gisaeng]], dancer, writer, artist, and poet during the [[Korea]]n [[Joseon Dynasty]]s of the 15th century from the first noble family of dancers, prostitutes. Her [[Gisaeng]] name was '''Gamdong'''. She is one of [[Korea]]'s legendary dancers of the 15th century.

== Life ==
She was from noble families of the [[Korea]]n [[Joseon Dynasty]], her father was [[Yu Guisu]] (유귀수 ; 兪龜壽), [[Mayor of Hanseong]].<ref>The current mayor of Seoul</ref> she wrote poetry and painted pictures well. However, much work has been destroyed or have not been preserved.

In early years she was arranged to marry [[Choi Jungki]] (최중기 ; 崔仲基), a county governor and head of a [[myeon (administrative division)|myeon]].<ref name="divorced1">[http://people.aks.ac.kr/front/tabCon/ppl/pplView.aks?pplId=PPL_6JOa_A9999_2_0018457 Yu Gam-dong]</ref>

She was raped by [[Kim Yeo-dal]] (김여달; 金如達) and divorced, later becoming a Gisaeng.<ref>[http://100.naver.com/100.nhn?docid=748101 Gam-dong:Naver] {{ko}}</ref> She was a Gisaeng, dancer, and poet.

As a divorced woman, she became known for her love life, having numerous male lovers, something extremely controversial in Korean society at that time.<ref name="divorced1"/>

